on ‘Ga naar het erkenningenloket’; log in with eID).</p><p>If you do not have a Belgian eID, you should register the company by registered letter with the Flemish administration before being allowed to work in the Flemish Region. Send your notification by registered letter to Departement Omgeving, Koning Albert II-laan 20/bus 8, 1000 Brussel, to the attention of Team Erkenningen, afdeling GOP.</p><p>Attach the following information to your notification:</p><ul><li>a copy of the European certificate as a fire protection equipment company in Dutch, French, German or English</li><li>the official name of the company</li><li>the company registration number. If the company does not have a company registration number, you should submit the address of the registered office and the VAT number of the company</li><li>the telephone number and the e-mail address</li><li>an overview of the recognised fire protection equipment technicians employed, including copies of their Flemish recognition.</li></ul><p>he recognition will take effect from the date on which this information is submitted to the Flemish administration. The company then receives a Flemish recognition certificate from the Energy and Climate Agency of Flanders and is included on the list of <a href=\"https://datasets.omgeving.vlaanderen.be/be.vl.omgeving.erkenningen.distribution.bedrijven_brandbeveiligingsapparatuur.pdf\">recognised fire protection equipment companies</a>.</p>",
